summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2011 MERCEDES-BENZ E550. WHEN THE DRIVER RETURNED TO HER PARKED VEHICLE, THE REAR OF THE VEHICLE WAS CRASHED. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO A COLLISION CENTER AND THE COSMETIC REPAIRS WERE PERFORMED. AFTERWARDS, THE CONTACT BEGAN TO EXPERIENCE A LEAK ABOVE THE REARVIEW MIRROR. THE FAILURE WAS PERSISTENT. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO A LOCAL DEALER (TAFEL MOTOR COMPANY 4156 SHELBYVILLE ROAD, LOUISVILLE, KY 40207), BUT THE CAUSE OF THE FAILURE WAS NOT DETERMINED. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT REPAIRED. THE VEHICLE WAS INSPECTED BY A SUN ROOF TECHNICIAN WHO DIAGNOSED THAT THE WINDSHIELD WAS DETACHED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE AND ADVISED THE CONTACT TO TAKE THE VEHICLE TO THE LOCAL DEALER. THE MANUFACTURER ALSO STATED THAT THERE WAS A RECALL FOR A DIFFERENT MODEL VEHICLE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS APPROXIMATELY 83,000.
